modules.description: Writes characters, strings, bytes, and bigstrings directly into a buffer. Accepts offset and length parameters to control the portion of the data written. Designed for efficient binary serialization workflows.

Schedules operations on Faraday.bigstring values with a specific ordering mechanism. It handles vector-based data structures and ensures execution order consistency. Used to manage buffer allocation and data streaming in network I/O pipelines.

Encodes and decodes binary data using a stream-based approach, supporting integers, strings, and nested structures. It processes data through a series of transformation steps defined by user-provided functions. This is useful for implementing network protocols or file format parsers that require precise byte-level control.

Writes characters, strings, bytes, and bigstrings into a buffer with precise control over offset and length, enabling efficient binary serialization. Manages operations on bigstring values, ensuring ordered execution for vector-based data structures, particularly useful in network I/O pipelines. Supports buffer allocation and data streaming by enforcing consistent operation sequencing. For example, it can serialize structured data into a pre-allocated buffer or manage incoming byte streams with guaranteed processing order.
